{"id": 225034708, "title": "Karol G to Be Honored With Woman of the Year at Billboard Latin Women\u00a0in\u00a0Music\u00a02024", "text": "Karol G is set to be honored with Woman of the Year at the Billboard Latin Women in Music 2024, Billboard and Telemundo announced on Wednesday (May 29). Just months after being named as Billboard\u2018s 2024 Woman of the Year in March, Karol will be recognized once more on June 9 for her extraordinary milestones and unparalleled impact on the music industry. The show will air exclusively on Telemundo at 9 p.m. ET, and will be simultaneously available on the Telemundo app and Peacock. Over the past few years, Karol G has become a force to be reckoned with. In 2023, Karol became the first female artist to top the Billboard 200 with a Spanish-language album thanks to Ma\u00f1ana Ser\u00e1 Bonito. She also kicked off her history-making stadium tour in support of the record-breaking set that includes hits like \u201cTQG\u201d with Shakira and \u201cProvenza\u201d. In March, she won her first Grammy, taking home best m\u00fasica urbana album for Ma\u00f1ana Ser\u00e1 Bonito. Additionally, Karol launched her Con Cora Foundation, which was established to continue the artist\u2019s social work and mission to support women who lead households, at-risk youth, children facing chronic or disabling diseases, those dealing with teenage pregnancy, women deprived of liberty and post-penalty, as well as low-income women. Karol G joins the previously announced lineup of powerhouse Latin women shaping the music industry. Honorees include Gloria Estefan who will receive the \u201cLegend\u201d award; Camila Cabello will receive the \u201cGlobal Impact\u201d award; Ana B\u00e1rbara the \u201cLifetime Achievement\u201d award; \u00c1ngela Aguilar who will receive the \u201cMusical Dynasty\u201d award; Kali Uchis who will receive the \u201cRising Star\u201d award; and Kany Garc\u00eda who will receive the \u201cSpirit of Change\u201d award. The Billboard Latin Women in Music franchise recognizes the importance of Latin women in the music industry and honors those who have positively impacted Latin music and the industry the previous year. The honors bestowed in 2023 included Shakira as \u201cWoman of the Year,\u201d Ana Gabriel as \u201cLiving Legend,\u201d Emilia as \u201cRising Star,\u201d and Thalia as \u201cGlobal Powerhouse,\u201d among others. In the coming weeks, additional honorees and details will be announced for the second annual Billboard Latin Women in Music ceremony.", "summary": "The Colombian hitmaker was also Billboard\u2019s 2024 Woman of the\u00a0Year in March.", "url": "https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/karol-g-woman-of-the-year-latin-women-in-music-1235694562/", "image": "https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/karol-g-01-red-carpet-wim-2024-billboard-1548.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 13:00:00", "author": "Griselda Flores", "authors": ["Griselda Flores"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": 0.683}